    "message_1": "What is the moving average of the following time series data of monthly sales for the years 2019 and 2020, with a window size of 3 months?\n\n2019: 20,000; 24,000; 21,000; 19,000; 23,000; 26,000; 28,000; 32,000; 29,000; 27,000; 26,000; 30,000 \n\n2020: 31,000; 28,000; 25,000; 22,000; 24,000; 28,000; 27,000; 29,000; 33,000; 30,000; 39,000; 42,000",
    "message_2": "To calculate the moving average with a window size of 3 months, we will take the average of every 3 consecutive months' sales data.\n\n2019:\n(20,000 + 24,000 + 21,000) / 3 = 21,667\n(24,000 + 21,000 + 19,000) / 3 = 21,333\n(21,000 + 19,000 + 23,000) / 3 = 21,000\n(19,000 + 23,000 + 26,000) / 3 = 22,667\n(23,000 + 26,000 + 28,000) / 3 = 25,667\n(26,000 + 28,000 + 32,000) / 3 = 28,667\n(28,000 + 32,000 + 29,000) / 3 = 29,667\n(32,000 + 29,000 + 27,000) / 3 = 29,333\n(29,000 + 27,000 + 26,000) / 3 = 27,333\n(27,000 + 26,000 + 30,000) / 3 = 27,667\n\n2020:\n(31,000 + 28,000 + 25,000) / 3 = 28,000\n(28,000 + 25,000 + 22,000) / 3 = 25,000\n(25,000 + 22,000 + 24,000) / 3 = 23,667\n(22,000 + 24,000 + 28,000) / 3 = 24,667\n(24,000 + 28,000 + 27,000) / 3 = 26,333\n(28,000 + 27,000 + 29,000) / 3 = 28,000\n(27,000 + 29,000 + 33,000) / 3 = 29,667\n(29,000 + 33,000 + 30,000) / 3 = 30,667\n(33,000 + 30,000 + 39,000) / 3 = 34,000\n(30,000 + 39,000 + 42,000) / 3 = 37,000\n\nThe moving averages for the given data are:\n\n2019: 21,667; 21,333; 21,000; 22,667; 25,667; 28,667; 29,667; 29,333; 27,333; 27,667\n\n2020: 28,000; 25,000; 23,667; 24,667; 26,333; 28,000; 29,667; 30,667; 34,000; 37,000"
